{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "kjva:job.36",
    "translationId": "kjva",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 36,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 36",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 36 in King James Version with Apocrypha."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.36.1",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:1",
      "text": "Elihu also proceeded, and said,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.36.2",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:2",
      "text": "Suffer me a little, and I will shew thee that I have yet to speak on God’s behalf.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.36.3",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:3",
      "text": "I will fetch my knowledge from afar, and will ascribe righteousness to my Maker.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.36.4",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:4",
      "text": "For truly my words shall not be false: he that is perfect in knowledge is with thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.36.5",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:5",
      "text": "Behold, God is mighty, and despiseth not any: he is mighty in strength and wisdom.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.36.6",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:6",
      "text": "He preserveth not the life of the wicked: but giveth right to the poor.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.36.7",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:7",
      "text": "He withdraweth not his eyes from the righteous: but with kings are they on the throne; yea, he doth establish them for ever, and they are exalted.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.36.8",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:8",
      "text": "And if they be bound in fetters, and be holden in cords of affliction;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.36.9",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:9",
      "text": "Then he sheweth them their work, and their transgressions that they have exceeded.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.36.10",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:10",
      "text": "He openeth also their ear to discipline, and commandeth that they return from iniquity.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.36.11",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:11",
      "text": "If they obey and serve him, they shall spend their days in prosperity, and their years in pleasures.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.36.12",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:12",
      "text": "But if they obey not, they shall perish by the sword, and they shall die without knowledge.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.36.13",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:13",
      "text": "But the hypocrites in heart heap up wrath: they cry not when he bindeth them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.36.14",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:14",
      "text": "They die in youth, and their life is among the unclean.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.36.15",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:15",
      "text": "He delivereth the poor in his affliction, and openeth their ears in oppression.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.36.16",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:16",
      "text": "Even so would he have removed thee out of the strait into a broad place, where there is no straitness; and that which should be set on thy table should be full of fatness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.36.17",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:17",
      "text": "But thou hast fulfilled the judgment of the wicked: judgment and justice take hold on thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.36.18",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:18",
      "text": "Because there is wrath, beware lest he take thee away with his stroke: then a great ransom cannot deliver thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.36.19",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:19",
      "text": "Will he esteem thy riches? no, not gold, nor all the forces of strength.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.36.20",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:20",
      "text": "Desire not the night, when people are cut off in their place.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.36.21",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:21",
      "text": "Take heed, regard not iniquity: for this hast thou chosen rather than affliction.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.36.22",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:22",
      "text": "Behold, God exalteth by his power: who teacheth like him?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.36.23",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:23",
      "text": "Who hath enjoined him his way? or who can say, Thou hast wrought iniquity?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.36.24",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:24",
      "text": "Remember that thou magnify his work, which men behold.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.36.25",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:25",
      "text": "Every man may see it; man may behold it afar off.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.36.26",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:26",
      "text": "Behold, God is great, and we know him not, neither can the number of his years be searched out.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.36.27",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:27",
      "text": "For he maketh small the drops of water: they pour down rain according to the vapour thereof:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.36.28",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:28",
      "text": "Which the clouds do drop and distil upon man abundantly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.36.29",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:29",
      "text": "Also can any understand the spreadings of the clouds, or the noise of his tabernacle?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.36.30",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:30",
      "text": "Behold, he spreadeth his light upon it, and covereth the bottom of the sea.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.36.31",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:31",
      "text": "For by them judgeth he the people; he giveth meat in abundance.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.36.32",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:32",
      "text": "With clouds he covereth the light; and commandeth it not to shine by the cloud that cometh betwixt.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.36.33",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 36,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 36:33",
      "text": "The noise thereof sheweth concerning it, the cattle also concerning the vapour.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
